cs.CG, cs.RO, cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.GT 

The paper deals with planar linkages and their reconfigurability, which falls under computational geometry (cs.CG) and robotics (cs.RO). The use of annotated configuration spaces and topological arguments suggests a connection to discrete mathematics and theoretical computer science (cs.DS), as well as control systems and dynamical systems (cs.SY). Finally, the mention of universal reconfigurability results and convex cones suggests a connection to geometric topology (cs.GT).
